  "response": "The time it takes to find a job after graduating can vary widely depending on factors like the job market, industry, location, and individual circumstances. Some graduates may secure a position almost immediately after graduation, while others might take several months or longer. On average, many graduates find jobs within three to six months, but this can differ greatly. Networking, internships, and job search strategies can significantly influence the timeline as well.",
